      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This high-revving masterpiece utilizes individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure Double VANOS system for optimized cam phasing across the entire RPM range. Power is delivered through a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to a variable M-differential lock. The chassis is structurally flawless; the rear subframe mounting points have been professionally reinforced to prevent common floor-pan fatigue. The suspension retains factory geometry with fresh bushings and dampers, ensuring the original turn-in precision. Maintenance is exhaustive, including recent valve clearance adjustments and preventative rod bearing replacement using ARP hardware. The exterior maintains its factory-delivered luster with no orange peel or paint depth inconsistencies, and the interior Nappa leather remains supple with no bolster wear.",
